## Status: NO LICENSE FILE FOUND

The upstream source repository contains no LICENSE, COPYING, or NOTICE file.
The README does not mention a license.

This is a known risk (documented in plans/stage2/01-copy-and-export-injection.md).
Before any redistribution or production use, the license must be confirmed with
the author (iniwex5).

## What was copied

- `pkg/qmi/` → `qmi/` (34 Go files) — QMI protocol stack (QMUX framing,
  service wrappers: WDS/WDA/DMS/NAS/UIM/WMS/IMS/VOICE)
- `pkg/netcfg/` → `netcfg/` (8 Go files) — platform network configuration
  (Linux/macOS/Windows, used in stage 3)

## What was NOT copied

- `pkg/manager/` — couples to Linux device discovery (subplan 07 decision)
- `pkg/device/` — Linux sysfs device discovery

## Modifications

- `transport_export.go` added: exports `Transport` (alias for `qmiTransport`)
  and `NewClientFromTransport()` — the injection point for user-space USB
  transport (bypasses /dev/cdc-wdm0 kernel driver dependency).
- No other source files modified.
